","path":null,"size_bytes":9951,"size_tokens":null},"docs/mobile-integration-guide.md":{"content":"# MedInvest Watch App - Mobile Integration Guide

## Overview

This guide explains how the Apple Watch companion app connects to the MedInvest backend API, and how to configure the endpoints for development and production environments.

---

## Backend API Endpoints

All endpoints are served from the Express.js backend (default port 5000). The watch app communicates directly with these REST endpoints.

### Feed & Posts

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/watch/feed` | GET | Paginated feed with room filtering |
| `/api/watch/posts/:id` | GET | Single post detail |
| `/api/watch/posts/:id/vote` | POST | Vote on a post (up/down/null) |
| `/api/watch/posts/:id/bookmark` | POST | Bookmark a post |
| `/api/watch/posts/:id/bookmark` | DELETE | Remove bookmark |
| `/api/watch/posts/:id/comments` | GET | Comments for a post |
| `/api/watch/trending` | GET | Top 5 trending posts by score |

### Rooms & Navigation

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/watch/rooms` | GET | All 8 room categories |

### Notifications

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/notifications` | GET | Full notifications (mobile) |
| `/api/watch/notifications` | GET | Compact notifications (watch) |

### System

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/watch/sync/status` | GET | Sync status and last update time |
| `/api/health` | GET | Server health check |

---

## Room Categories (8 rooms)

Both the watch app and mobile app use these 8 room categories:

| ID | Name | Slug | Icon | Color |
|----|------|------|------|-------|
| 1 | General | `general` | G | #6B7280 |
| 2 | Biotech | `biotech` | B | #10B981 |
| 3 | MedTech | `medtech` | M | #3B82F6 |
| 4 | Pharma | `pharma` | P | #8B5CF6 |
| 5 | Digital Health | `digital-health` | D | #EC4899 |
| 6 | Diagnostics | `diagnostics` | X | #F59E0B |
| 7 | Genomics | `genomics` | G | #14B8A6 |
| 8 | Healthcare AI | `healthcare-ai` | A | #6366F1 |

---

## API Request/Response Formats

### GET /api/watch/feed

**Query Parameters:**
- `cursor` (optional) - Pagination cursor from previous response
- `room` (optional) - Room slug to filter by (e.g., `biotech`)
- `page_size` (optional) - Number of posts per page (default: 5)

**Response:**
```json
{
  "posts": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "content": "Post content...",
      "author": {
        "id": 1,
        "username": "dr_chen",
        "full_name": "Dr. Sarah Chen",
        "avatar_url": null,
        "specialty": "Oncology",
        "is_verified": true
      },
      "room": {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "Biotech",
        "slug": "biotech",
        "icon": "B",
        "color": "#10B981"
      },
      "hashtags": ["#biotech", "#CRISPR"],
      "upvotes": 42,
      "downvotes": 3,
      "comments_count": 12,
      "feed_score": 147,
      "is_anonymous": false,
      "anonymous_name": null,
      "user_vote": null,
      "is_bookmarked": false,
      "created_at": "2026-02-08T10:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "has_more": true,
  "next_cursor": "2",
  "total": 20
}
```

### POST /api/watch/posts/:id/vote

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "direction": "up"  // "up", "down", or null to remove vote
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "post": { /* updated post object */ }
}
```

### GET /api/watch/posts/:id/comments

**Response:**
```json
{
  "comments": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "post_id": 1,
      "author": {
        "id": 10,
        "username": "dr_wong",
        "full_name": "Dr. Kevin Wong",
        "avatar_url": null,
        "specialty": "Molecular Biology",
        "is_verified": true
      },
      "content": "Fascinating research...",
      "upvotes": 8,
      "created_at": "2026-02-08T09:30:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "total": 4
}
```

### GET /api/watch/trending

**Response:**
```json
{
  "posts": [ /* top 5 posts by feed_score */ ],
  "updated_at": "2026-02-08T12:00:00.000Z"
}
```

### GET /api/watch/notifications

**Response:**
```json
{
  "notifications": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "comment",
      "title": "New Comment",
      "message": "Dr. Chen commented on your post about CRISPR therapy",
      "compact": "Dr. Chen commented on your post",
      "read": false,
      "created_at": "2026-02-08T11:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "unread_count": 3
}
```

---

## Watch App Setup (Xcode)

### Step-by-Step: Create Watch App in Xcode

The complete watch app source code is in `watch-app/MedInvestWatch/` (18 Swift files). To build it in Xcode:

1. **Create Xcode Project**: File > New > Project > watchOS > App
   - Product Name: `MedInvest Watch`
   - Bundle Identifier: `com.medinvest.watch`
   - Interface: SwiftUI
   - Language: Swift
   - Include Notification Scene: Yes
   - Include Complication: Yes

2. **Copy Source Files**: Drag all files from `watch-app/MedInvestWatch/` into your Xcode project, preserving the folder structure

3. **Set API Base URL**: Open `Services/APIClient.swift` and replace `YOUR-REPL-NAME` with your actual Replit deployment URL

4. **Build & Run**: Select an Apple Watch simulator or paired device and hit Run

### Source File Reference (18 files)

```
watch-app/MedInvestWatch/
├── MedInvestWatchApp.swift           # App entry point with WatchConnectivity setup
├── ContentView.swift                  # Root NavigationStack
├── FeedViewModel.swift                # Observable feed state (pagination, room filter)
├── Models/
│   ├── Post.swift                     # Post, Author, Comment, VoteDirection models
│   ├── Room.swift                     # Room struct + RoomCategory enum (8 categories)
│   └── FeedResponse.swift             # All API response types
├── Views/
│   ├── FeedView.swift                 # Main feed with room filter + skeleton loading
│   ├── PostRowView.swift              # Feed card with vital pulse animation
│   ├── PostDetailView.swift           # Full post with vote/bookmark actions + haptics
│   ├── RoomFilterView.swift           # Room picker sheet (8 rooms)
│   └── SyncStatusView.swift           # Backend connection status
├── Services/
│   ├── APIClient.swift                # All API calls to MedInvest backend
│   ├── AuthService.swift              # Keychain token storage
│   └── WatchConnector.swift           # WatchConnectivity bridge to iPhone
├── Components/
│   └── VitalPulseEffect.swift         # Signature animation modifier
├── Extensions/
│   ├── Color+Hex.swift                # Medical color palette + hex initializer
│   └── TimeFormatting.swift           # ISO 8601 to relative time ("2h", "3d")
└── Complications/
    └── ComplicationViews.swift        # Watch face widgets (circular, rectangular, inline)
```

### Setting the API Base URL

In `APIClient.swift`, update the base URL to your deployed MedInvest backend:

```swift
// For development (Replit URL):
private let baseURL = "https://your-repl-name.replit.dev"

// For production:
private let baseURL = "https://your-production-domain.com"
```

### Connecting Watch to Replit Backend

1. Publish your MedInvest app on Replit to get a stable URL
2. Copy the published URL (e.g., `https://medinvest.replit.app`)
3. Paste it into `APIClient.swift` as the `baseURL`
4. Test connectivity: your watch will hit `GET /api/health` first
5. The watch app and mobile app share the same backend -- votes, bookmarks, and feed data are synchronized

### Watch Complications

Use the `/api/watch/trending` endpoint to power watch complications:
- Show the top trending post title
- Update every 15-30 minutes via `TimelineProvider`
- Display the trending post's room color as the complication tint

---

## Data Flow Architecture

```
Watch App (SwiftUI)
    |
    ├── FeedView → GET /api/watch/feed?room=biotech&cursor=2
    ├── PostDetailView → GET /api/watch/posts/1
    │   └── CommentsView → GET /api/watch/posts/1/comments
    ├── TrendingView → GET /api/watch/trending
    ├── NotificationsView → GET /api/watch/notifications
    ├── RoomPickerView → GET /api/watch/rooms
    ├── VoteAction → POST /api/watch/posts/1/vote
    └── BookmarkAction → POST/DELETE /api/watch/posts/1/bookmark

Mobile App (React Native/Expo)
    |
    ├── HomeScreen → GET /api/watch/feed (shared endpoint)
    ├── PostDetailScreen → GET /api/watch/posts/:id
    │   └── Comments → GET /api/watch/posts/:id/comments
    ├── NotificationsScreen → GET /api/notifications (full version)
    ├── VoteAction → POST /api/watch/posts/:id/vote
    └── BookmarkAction → POST/DELETE /api/watch/posts/:id/bookmark
```

---

## Color Constants (Shared)

Both apps should use these medical-themed colors:

| Name | Hex | Usage |
|------|-----|-------|
| Medical Blue | #00A3E0 | Primary actions, links |
| Alert Red | #FF6B6B | Downvotes, warnings |
| Vitality Green | #4CAF50 | Upvotes, success states |
| Surface Dark | #1C1C1E | Card backgrounds (dark mode) |
| Text Secondary | #8E8E93 | Timestamps, metadata |

---

## Testing Checklist

Before deploying, verify these scenarios work on both platforms:

- [ ] Feed loads with 20 posts across all 8 rooms
- [ ] Room filtering returns correct posts
- [ ] Pagination works (5 posts per page = 4 pages total)
- [ ] Voting updates counts and persists user vote state
- [ ] Bookmarking toggles correctly
- [ ] Comments load for each post
- [ ] Trending returns top 5 posts sorted by score
- [ ] Watch notifications include compact text
- [ ] Unread notification badge shows correct count
- [ ] Health endpoint returns 200 OK
